                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Careful.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red.</seg>
                        <date>Second half of the 19th century.</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; names of the king, of the patriarch of
                           Alexandria and of the metropolitan; incipit of Text I; directives to the
                           minister; name or initial words of the prayers to be read; elements of
                           the punctuation signs; elements of the Ethiopic numerals. 
 On the
                           incipit page of Text I (fol. 3r), few lines are rubricated, alternating
                           with black lines.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">Starting from <locus target="#43r">43r</locus>, the scribe used a smaller
                        script.</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- Daily readings are indicated by the names of the
                              days of the week crudely written in the upper margin, in a recent
                              secondary hand, in blue pen: መቅድም፡ ዘዘወትር: <locus target="#3r">fol.
                                 3r</locus>. ዘሰኑይ: <locus target="#6r">fol. 6r</locus>. ዘሠሉስ: <locus target="#9v">fol. 9v</locus>. ዘረቡዕ: <locus target="#14r">fol.
                                 14r</locus>. ዘሐሙስ: <locus target="#17r">fol. 17r</locus>. ዘዓርብ:
                                 <locus target="#20v">fol. 20v</locus>. ዘቀዳም: <locus target="#21v">fol. 21v</locus>. ዘሰንበት: <locus target="#23r">fol.
                              23r</locus>.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e3">
                           <desc>- One line was not used by the scribe because of a hole: <locus target="#23va">fol.  23va</locus>. - Two lines were written in place of one line, in smaller script: <locus target="#24ra">fol.  24ra</locus>, 50rb.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding contemporary="true">
                        <decoNote xml:id="b1">Two wooden boards covered with reddish-brown tooled
                           leather cover.
 Two pairs of sewing stations.</decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="bindingMaterial">
